cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper is about improving the performance of machine learning models for click-through rate (CTR) prediction and query-ad relevance matching in sponsored search. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with search engines and information retrieval systems. The paper also proposes a novel cohort negative sampling technique, which involves learning implicit negative signals, suggesting a possible connection to natural language processing (NLP) and sentiment analysis, which are covered in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep neural architectures for CTR prediction and query-ad relevance matching suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of semantic embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and NLP.
